Use the Paragraph Designer to edit existing formats or create new paragraph tags in the Paragraph Catalog. The Paragraph Designer also allows you to define bullet and numbered lists and adjust tab spacing for numbered lists.

To edit a numbered list using the Paragraph Designer:

From the menu bar, select Format. A drop-down menu opens.

Select Paragraph. A sub-menu opens.

Choose Designer to open the Paragraph Designer window.

Select the Numbering tab.

From the Paragraph Tag list, select Numbered.

Choose <n+> to set the number format. Any text that appears after <n+> will display after the number in the document.

Select /t to insert one tab space.

Click Update All to apply the changes.


